&lt;p&gt;BRPH is a nationally recognized, employee-owned architecture, engineering, and construction services firm delivering innovative solutions for clients across the aerospace, commercial, defense, education, entertainment, hospitality, and manufacturing sectors. Our collaborative, multidisciplinary teams partner with clients to solve complex challenges and create facilities that shape communities and industries.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an Early Career Structural Engineer (EI/EIT), you will join a team of experienced structural professionals supporting projects ranging from facility assessments and renovations to complex new construction across a diverse portfolio of market sectors. Working alongside licensed Professional Engineers, you will gain hands-on experience in structural analysis, design, construction administration, and multidisciplinary coordination while building the technical foundation necessary for Professional Engineer (PE) licensure and long-term career growth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At BRPH, we invest in our people through mentorship, technical training, employee ownership, and progressive project responsibilities that provide meaningful opportunities for professional development and advancement.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SUMMARY:&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;The Structural Engineer (EI/EIT) will utilize engineering knowledge, judgment, and design software to perform structural analysis, design, and preparation of construction documents under the supervision of licensed Professional Engineers. The individual will contribute to the design and delivery of routine structural projects and key components of larger multidisciplinary projects while continuing to develop technical expertise, project coordination skills, and professional engineering judgment.&lt;/p&gt;
